cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on learning interpretable feature representations for medical image analysis, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a self-supervised objective to improve disentanglement, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for predicting future frames, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies these techniques to improve semi-supervised segmentation, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM).
